our|LMCT|dir1=north|city1=Menominee|city2=Escanaba<!--on distance signs after US 141 split-->}}\n|notes=Continuation into Michigan\n}}\n{{jctbtm|exit|keys=concur,incomplete,unbuilt}}\n\n==See also==\n*{{portal-inline|U.S. Roads}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|U.S. Route 41 in Wisconsin}}\n{{Attached KML|display=title,inline}}\n* [http://wisconsindot.gov/Pages/projects/by-region/ne/us41interstate/default.aspx Official US&nbsp;41 Interstate conversion project page]\n* [http://www.dot.wisconsin.gov/projects/neregion/41/docs/brochure.pdf Official US&nbsp;41 conversion brochure (PDF)]\n\n{{state detail page browse|type=US|route=41|state=Wisconsin|statebefore=Illinois|stateafter=Michigan}}\n\n[[Category:U.S. Highways in Wisconsin|41]]\n[[Category:U.S. Route 41| Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Freeways in the Milwaukee area]]\n[[Category:Lake Michigan Circle Tour]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Kenosha County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Racine County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Milwaukee County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Waukesha County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Washington County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Dodge County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Fond du Lac County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Winnebago County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Outagamie County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Brown County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Oconto County, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Transportation in Marinette County, Wisconsin]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Section of U.S. Highway in Wisconsin}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2012}}\n{{highway detail hatnote|U.S. Route 41}}\n{{Infobox road\n|state=WI\n|type=US\n|route=41\n|map={{maplink|frame=yes|plain=yes|frame-align=center|frame-width=290|frame-lat=44.011|frame-long=-88.448|zoom=6|type=line|raw={{Wikipedia:Map data/Wikipedia KML/U.S. Route 41 in Wisconsin}}}}\n|map_custom=yes\n|map_notes=US&nbsp;41 highlighted in red\n|length_mi=225\n|length_ref=\n|length_round=\n|established=1926\n|direction_a=South\n|direction_b=North\n|terminus_a={{jct|state=IL|I|41|I|94|US|41}} near [[Pleasant Prairie, Wisconsin|Pleasant Prairie]]\n|junction={{plainlist|1=\n*{{jct|state=WI|I|43|I|94|I|894}} in [[Milwaukee, Wisconsin|Milwaukee]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|I|43|US|45}} in Milwaukee\n*{{jct|state=WI|I|94|I|894}} in Milwaukee\n*{{jct|state=WI|US|151}} in [[Fond du Lac, Wisconsin|Fond du Lac]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|WI|23}} in [[Fond du Lac, Wisconsin|Fond du Lac]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|US|45}} in [[Oshkosh, Wisconsin|Oshkosh]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|US|10}} in [[Fox Crossing, Wisconsin|Fox Crossing]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|US|141}} in [[Green Bay, Wisconsin|Green Bay]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|I|41|I|43}} in [[Howard, Wisconsin|Howard]]\n*{{jct|state=WI|US|141}} in [[Abrams, Wisconsin|Abrams]]}}\n|terminus_b={{jct|state=MI|US|41}} at [[Marinette, Wisconsin|Marinette]]\n|counties=[[Kenosha County, Wisconsin|Kenosha]], [[Racine County, Wisconsin|Racine]], [[Milwaukee County, Wisconsin|Milwaukee]], [[Waukesha County, Wisconsin|Waukesha]], [[Washington County, Wisconsin|Washington]], [[Dodge County, Wisconsin|Dodge]], [[Fond du Lac County, Wisconsin|Fond du Lac]], [[Winnebago County, Wisconsin|Winnebago]], [[Outagamie County, Wisconsin|Outagamie]], [[Brown County, Wisconsin|Brown]], [[Oconto County, Wisconsin|Oconto]], [[Marinette County, Wisconsin|Marinette]]\n|previous_type=I\n|previous_route=41\n|next_type=WI\n|next_route=41\n\n}}\n'''U.S. Highway 41''' ('''US&nbsp;41''') is a north\u2013south highway [[United States Numbered Highway]] in eastern [[Wisconsin]]. It runs from [[Pleasant Prairie, Wisconsin|Pleasant Prairie]] on the [[Illinois]] border north to [[Marinette, Wisconsin|Marinette]] on the [[Michigan]] border. Most of the route is concurrent with [[Interstate 41]] in the state, with the exception of the portion between [[Howard, Wisconsin|Howard]], a suburb of [[Green Bay, Wisconsin|Green Bay]],  and [[Marinette, Wisconsin|Marinette]].\n\n==Route description==\nUS&nbsp;41 is a [[freeway]] for nearly 85&nbsp;percent of its route through Wisconsin, with the exceptions being a {{convert|29|mi|km|adj=on}} [[limited-access road|expressway]] section from the US 141 interchange in [[Oconto County, Wisconsin|Oconto County]] to Marinette and a {{convert|5|mi|km|adj=on|spell=in}} surface arterial section within Marinette. The highway [[concurrency (road)|runs concurrently]] with I-94 from Milwaukee to the Illinois border and concurrently with I-41 from Howard to the Illinois border.\n\nUS&nbsp;41 runs northwest from Milwaukee and passes [[Fond du Lac, Wisconsin|Fond du Lac]], [[Oshkosh, Wisconsin|Oshkosh]], and [[Appleton, Wisconsin|Appleton]] before heading to Green Bay. The route is a major access point for [[Miller Park (Milwaukee)|Miller Park]], home of the [[Milwaukee Brewers]] [[Major League Baseball]] club, the [[EAA AirVenture Oshkosh]] air show in Oshkosh, and for [[Lambeau Field]], the home of the [[Green Bay Packers]] [[NFL]] football team.\n\nAfter leaving Green Bay, US&nbsp;41 continues north to [[Abrams, Wisconsin|Abrams]] co-signed with [[U.S. Route 141|US&nbsp;141]], and then it turns east off the co-signed route toward Marinette and into Michigan.\n\n==History==\nThe first alignment of US 41 in Wisconsin, which extended south from Marinette to the Illinois state line, was defined generally by two state trunk highways in existence in 1926: [[Wisconsin Highway 15|WIS&nbsp;15]] from Marinette to Milwaukee, and [[Wisconsin Highway 57|WIS&nbsp;57]] from Milwaukee to the Illinois state line. Signs for the newly established highway were to be placed in spring of 1927.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news |url = https://www.newspapers.com/image/287475637 |title = State Prepares to Mark New U.S. Thru Highways |last =  |first =  |date = August 18, 1926 |work = Appleton Post-Crescent |access-date = December 23, 2017 |page = 7 |language = en |via = Newspapers.com }}</ref> A meeting of the Wisconsin Highway Commission in 1926 decided that no new U.S. Highway number would overlap with an existing state route number; therefore, [[Wisconsin Highway 41|WIS&nbsp;41]] was retired and renumbered when US 41 came into existence.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nIn Milwaukee the original routing of US&nbsp;41 used Lisbon Avenue east to North 27th Street, then south along that road to the Illinois state line. After the Stadium Freeway was built in the 1960s, US&nbsp;41 followed that road from Lisbon Avenue south across I-94 to National Avenue and then east to 27th Street, which is known as Layton Boulevard between National Avenue and Lincoln Avenue. WisDOT rerouted US&nbsp;41 along I-94 from the Stadium Interchange to the Illinois state line, removed Layton Boulevard north of Forest Home Avenue from the state highway system and gave Layton Boulevard and 27th Street south of Forest Home Avenue the designation of [[Wisconsin Highway 241|WIS&nbsp;241]] in a compromise to avoid expansion of the original route. The old US&nbsp;41 freeway section south of I-94 to National Avenue (which was realigned to accommodate the construction of [[Miller Park (Milwaukee)|Miller Park]]) was designated [[Wisconsin Highway 341|WIS&nbsp;341]] but is unsigned. Trailblazer signs label it Miller Park Way.\n\nBy 1955, US&nbsp;41 was relocated from the corridor of today's [[Wisconsin Highway 175|WIS&nbsp;175]] and its successors to a nearby expressway in [[Winnebago County, Wisconsin|Winnebago]], [[Fond du Lac County, Wisconsin|Fond du Lac]], [[Dodge County, Wisconsin|Dodge]], [[Washington County, Wisconsin|Washington]], [[Waukesha County, Wisconsin|Waukesha]], and [[Milwaukee County, Wisconsin|Milwaukee]] Counties.<ref name=\"bessert01\">{{cite web |first = Christopher J. |last = Bessert |title = US&nbsp;41, The Complete History |work = Wisconsin Highways |publisher = Self-published |date = January 31, 2009 |url = http://www.wisconsinhighways.org/indepth/US-41_history.html |accessdate = December 14, 2006 }}{{SPS|certain=y|date= August 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn [[Green Bay, Wisconsin|Green Bay]], the road was rerouted in 1953 to make a curve to the right west of [[De Pere, Wisconsin|De Pere]], going onto Ashland Avenue to the Green Bay city limits. It then turned left onto Highland Avenue (after 1968, Lombardi Avenue), going past [[Lambeau Field]] and curving right onto Military Avenue. It then turned left at Velp Avenue. US 41 then followed present day Velp Avenue north to Suamico where it merged with what is now the US&nbsp;41 freeway. Until 1968 this was the outer highway for Green Bay; the area now is urbanized. The 1953\u20131968 Green Bay bypass was once again bypassed, sequentially, with the present US&nbsp;41 freeway beginning at Velp, southerly to Lombardi in 1968; Velp north to Suamico in 1971; then from Lombardi south to De Pere in 1974.<ref name=\"bessert01\"/>\n\n[[Appleton, Wisconsin|Appleton]] also saw US&nbsp;41 realignments over the course of time, beginning with the 1937 two-lane bypass (along the present freeway route) from [[Neenah, Wisconsin|Neenah]] northerly to a T-intersection with US&nbsp;10 (today's Wisconsin Avenue, [[Wisconsin Highway 96|WIS&nbsp;96]]). There, US&nbsp;41 turned east with US&nbsp;10, back to its original route at the intersection of US&nbsp;10 (Wisconsin Avenue) and Richmond Street north of downtown Appleton, then north on Richmond to present day Northland Avenue. There it turned east on new alignment back to the original route northeast of [[Kaukauna, Wisconsin|Kaukauna]]. In 1940, US&nbsp;41 was extended northerly from the T-intersection at US&nbsp;10 for {{convert|1|mi|km|spell=in}}, before making a large sweeping curve onto present day Northland Avenue to join back up with the previous bypass at Richmond Street. By 1962, the original Appleton bypass had been converted to four-lane divided highway from Oshkosh north to Northland Avenue, then north and east on new alignment bypassing the Northland Avenue bypass with the current freeway easterly to Kaukauna.\n\n==Exit list==\n{{mileposts}}\n{{jcttop|exit|length_ref=<ref name=\"WisDOT\">Wisconsin State Trunk Highway Logs:<br/>\n*{{cite book |author = Southeast Region Staff |title = State Trunk Highway Log for Southeast Region |date = December 31, 2008 |publisher = Wisconsin Department of Transportation |location = Waukesha, WI |type = XLS |at = 041N }}\n*{{cite book |author = Southwest Region Staff |title = State Trunk Highway Log for Southwest Region |date = December 31, 2008 |publisher = Wisconsin Department of Transportation |location = Madison, WI |type = XLS |at = 041N }}\n*{{cite book |author = Northeast Region Staff |title = State Trunk Highway Log for Region&nbsp;3 |date = May 14, 2009 |publisher = Wisconsin Department of Transportation |location = Green Bay, WI |pages = 172\u2013200 }}</ref>\n|exit_ref=<ref name=\"WisDOT1\">{{cite web |author = Staff |publisher = Wisconsin Department of Transportation |title = Exit Numbers on US&nbsp;41 |url = http://www.dot.wisconsin.gov/travel/road/exits-us41.htm |accessdate = June 10, 2007 |url-status = dead |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070607163514/http://www.dot.wisconsin.gov/travel/road/exits-us41.htm |archivedate = June 7, 2007 |df = mdy-all }}</ref>}}\n{{WIint|exit\n|county=Kenosha\n|cspan=7\n|location=Pleasant Prairie\n|lspan=3\n|mile=0.00\n|road={{jct|state=IL|I|41|I|94|US|41|dir1=south|dir2=east|dir3=south|city1=Chicago}}\n|notes=Continuation into Illinois\n}}\n{{WIint|exit\n|mile=2.04\n|exit=347\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|165|CTH|Q|county2=Kenosha|name2=Lakeview Parkway}}\n|notes=Exit numbers follow I-94\n}}\n{{WIint|exit\n|mile=3.43\n|exit=345\n|road={{jct|state=WI|CTH|C|county1=Kenosha}}\n}}\n{{WIint|exit\n|location=Kenosha\n|mile=5.07\n|exit=344\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|50|city1=Kenosha|city2=Lake Geneva}}\n}}\n{{WIint|exit\n|location=Somers\n|lspan=2\n|mile=6.59\n|exit=342\n|road={{jct|state=WI|WI|158|city1=Keno