{"title_page": "Bodoland People's Front", "text_new": "{{short description|Political party in India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox Indian Political Party\n| party_name = Bodoland People's Front\n| colorcode  = {{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}\n| party_logo = [[File:BPF-Flag.svg|200px]]\n| chairman = [[Hagrama Mohilary]]\n| secretary = \n| ppchairman =  \n| loksabha_leader = \n| rajyasabha_leader = [[Biswajit Daimary]]\n| foundation = \n| alliance = [[National Democratic Alliance]] (NDA) , the regional alliance of [[North-East Democratic Alliance]] (NEDA)\n| loksabha_seats   = {{Composition bar|0|543|hex={{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}}}\n| rajyasabha_seats = {{Composition bar|1|245|hex={{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}}} \n| state_seats_name = [[Assam Legislative Assembly]]\n| state_seats      = {{Composition bar|12|126|hex={{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}}}\n| ideology = [[Secularism]]<br />[[Democracy]] <ref>{{cite web|title=IDEOLOGY & FLAG|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/#ideo|publisher=Election Commission of India|accessdate=9 May 2013|location=India|year=2013}}</ref>\n| headquarters = [[Kokrajhar]], [[Assam]]\n| eci = State Party<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Political Parties and Election Symbols main Notification Dated 18.01.2013|url=http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/ElectoralLaws/OrdersNotifications/ElecSym19012013_eng.pdf|publisher=Election Commission of India|accessdate=9 May 2013|location=India|year=2013}}</ref>\n| symbol = [[File:Indian Election Symbol Nangol.svg|150px|Nagol]]\n| website = {{url|http://www.bpfassam.in/}}\n}}\nThe '''Bodoland People's Front''' (BPF) is a state [[political party]] in [[Assam]], [[India]]. The party has its headquarters in [[Kokrajhar Town]] and currently is in power in the autonomous region of [[Bodoland]]. It is also an ally of [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] whose alliance known as [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|NDA]] formed the [[Government of Assam]] in 2016, it is also a member of the regional alliance of [[North East Democratic Alliance]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gogoi|first=Tarun|date=2019-06-01|title=North East Democratic Alliance (NEDA) and Political Change in Northeast India|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/338558276_North_East_Democratic_Alliance_NEDA_and_Political_Change_in_Northeast_India}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n== History ==\n\nThe BPF was formed as political party in year 2005<ref>[http://ceoassam.nic.in/election/AE2016/StarCampainer/Bodoland%20Peoples%20fonrt.pdf BPF Letter head indicating date of foundation</ref>, [[Hagrama Mohilary]] and Emmanuel Mosahary were selected as the President and the General Secretary of the new party. [[Hagrama Mohilary]] formed the first Elected Executive Bodoland Territorial Council after the end of the election. <ref>[https://www.academia.edu/38706042/BODOLAND_PEOPLES_FRONT-_ITS_NATURE_AND_ROLE_-_AN_ANALYTICAL_STUDY BODOLAND PEOPLES FRONT- ITS NATURE AND ROLE </ref><ref>[http://ijmr.net.in/download.php?filename=2017/July,-2017/SPKbbzYkGBjYdLK.pdf&new=IJMSS29July17-6696.pdf BJadav Ch. Basumatary Research Scholar, Bodoland University Dr. Jyotiraj Pathak Deptt. of Political Science, Bodoland University</ref><blockquote>Bodoland Peoples Front formed as per the resolution Vide No. 3, adopted in the Political convention held on 4th and 5th December 2005, as per BPF constitution<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/|title=BPF-Membership Registration System|website=www.bpfonline.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>, BPF shall bear true faith and allegiance to the constitution of India as established by law and to the principles of democracy, socialism and secularism as enshrined in the Indian Constitution, and also solemnly affirm our commitment to work for upholding the sovereignty, unity and integrity of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411202907/http://www.bpfassam.in/images/BPF%20Constitution_modify.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2014-04-11|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/|title=BPF-Membership Registration System|website=www.bpfonline.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>To work for strengthening the Indian Nationalism providing due respect to the identities of all sections of people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/#ideo|title=BPF-Membership Registration System|website=www.bpfonline.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n== Flag ==\nBPF flag is tri-colour with 3:2 size and having same significance as follows and Nangal in the middle of white colour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.relections.in/political-parties/bodoland-peoples-front.php#aboutparty|title=Bodoland People's Front, Bodoland People's Front News, Bodoland People's Front Lok Sabha Elections 2014 News|website=www.relections.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n== Lok Sabha Election ==\nIn the [[2009 Indian general election|2009 general election]] its candidate, [[Sansuma Khunggur Bwiswmuthiary]] was elected to the 15th [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Kokrajhar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kokrajhar]] constituency. [[Biswajit Daimary]] of this party was elected to the [[Rajya Sabha]] in May 2008. BPF had 10 members in the 12th [[Assam Legislative Assembly]] <ref>[https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/assam-polls-cong-sure-test-for-minority-party/story-Y77RSJdaaFCbd0oftLLC0I.html Assam polls: Cong sure, test for minority party]</ref>\n\n==Assembly election==\n\nIn the [[2011 Assam Legislative Assembly election|2011 Assam Assembly election]], BPF won 12 seats.In 2011, with 12 elected lawmakers, the BPF initially supported the [[Indian National Congress|Congress]] government, primarily because of the efforts of [[Himanta Biswa Sarma]], the former minister in the [[Tarun Gogoi]] government who later joined the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]].\n\nThe announcement was made on 19 January when Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] visits [[Kokrajhar]] headquarters of the autonomous [[Bodoland Territorial Council]] and announces a possible economic package of Rs 1000cr or the [[Bodoland Territorial Council]] area.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/BJP-forms-alliance-with-Bodoland-Peoples-Front-for-Assam-elections/articleshow/50617318.cms BJP forms alliance with Bodoland Peoples\u2019 Front for Assam elections]</ref>\n\nWith Assam heading for elections in 2016, [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] made its first alliance with the Bodoland People's Front in [[lower Assam]].In the [[2016 Assam Legislative Assembly election|2016 Assembly Elections]], the BPF won 12 seats and the alliance was established after [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] led [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]] which also includes [[Asom Gana Parishad]] formed its first government in [[Assam]] with [[Pramila Rani Brahma]] and [[Rihon Daimary]] sworn in as ministers in the [[Sarbananda Sonowal ministry (2016\u2013)|Sarbananda Sonowal ministry]]. Later during the cabinet expansion Shri [[Chandan Brahma]] was inducted as Cabinet minister for Tourism and other departments.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sentinelassam.com/north-east-india-news/assam-news/state-tourism-minister-chandan-brahma-inaugurates-community-hall-in-chirang/|title=State Tourism Minister Chandan Brahma inaugurates community hall in Chirang|date=2020-02-04|website=The Sentinel|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==North-East Democratic Alliance==\n\nIn May 2016, after the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] led [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]] formed its first government in [[Assam]], and formed a new alliance called the [[North-East Democratic Alliance]] (NEDA) with Himanta Biswa Sarma as its [[convener]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/himanta-biswa-sarma-named-convener-of-bjps-northeast-alliance-1409767|title=Himanta Biswa Sarma Named Convener Of BJP's Northeast Alliance|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> The Chief Ministers of the north eastern states of [[Sikkim]], [[Assam]] and [[Nagaland]] too belong to this alliance.<ref>http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/amit-shah-holds-meeting-with-northeast-cms-forms-alliance/story-YDYLQ6YsImuzZOQ6Zev5MO.html</ref>\n\n== Development in BTC ==\n\n=== Educational Institutions ===\n* Kokrajhar University, Kokrajhar\n\n* [[Central Institute of Technology, Kokrajhar]]\n\n* B.B. Engineering College, Chandrapara, Kokrajhar\n\n* Medical College, Besorgaon, Kokrajhar\n\n* Nursing College, Kokrajhar\n\nBTC chief Hagrama Mohilary laid the foundation stone of Udalguri Engineering College.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/foundation-stones-of-3-institutions-laid-colleges-at-kokrajhar-and-udalguri/cid/430568|title=Foundation stones of 3 institutions laid - Colleges at Kokrajhar and Udalguri|website=www.telegraphindia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nBTC chief Hagrama Mohilary  laid the foundation stone of a Rs 26-crore IT park at Onthai Gwlao, Chandamari, nearly 4km northwest of Kokrajhar town.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/foundationlaid-for-rs-26-crore-it-park/cid/429920|title=Foundationlaid for Rs 26-crore IT park|website=www.telegraphindia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Bodo Liberation Tigers Force]]\n* [[Bodo People's Progressive Front]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{India separatist movements}}\n{{Indian political parties}}\n{{North-East Democratic Alliance}}\n{{National Democratic Alliance |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties in India]]\n[[Category:State political parties in Assam]]\n[[Category:Bodoland]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Assam]]\n[[Category:Recognised state political parties in India]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1985]]\n[[Category:1985 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Bodoland People's Front]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Political party in India}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2015}}\n{{Infobox Indian Political Party\n| party_name = Bodoland People's Front\n| colorcode  = {{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}\n| party_logo = [[File:BPF-Flag.svg|200px]]\n| chairman = [[Hagrama Mohilary]]\n| secretary = \n| ppchairman =  \n| loksabha_leader = \n| rajyasabha_leader = [[Biswajit Daimary]]\n| foundation = \n| alliance = [[National Democratic Alliance]] (NDA) , the regional alliance of [[North-East Democratic Alliance]] (NEDA)\n| loksabha_seats   = {{Composition bar|0|245|hex={{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}}}\n| rajyasabha_seats = {{Composition bar|1|245|hex={{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}}} \n| state_seats_name = [[Assam Legislative Assembly]]\n| state_seats      = {{Composition bar|12|126|hex={{Bodoland People's Front/meta/color}}}}\n| ideology = [[Secularism]]<br />[[Democracy]] <ref>{{cite web|title=IDEOLOGY & FLAG|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/#ideo|publisher=Election Commission of India|accessdate=9 May 2013|location=India|year=2013}}</ref>\n| headquarters = [[Kokrajhar]], [[Assam]]\n| eci = State Party<ref>{{cite web|title=List of Political Parties and Election Symbols main Notification Dated 18.01.2013|url=http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/ElectoralLaws/OrdersNotifications/ElecSym19012013_eng.pdf|publisher=Election Commission of India|accessdate=9 May 2013|location=India|year=2013}}</ref>\n| symbol = [[File:Indian Election Symbol Nangol.svg|150px|Nagol]]\n| website = {{url|http://www.bpfassam.in/}}\n}}\nThe '''Bodoland People's Front''' (BPF) is a state [[political party]] in [[Assam]], [[India]]. The party has its headquarters in [[Kokrajhar Town]] and currently is in power in the autonomous region of [[Bodoland]]. It is also an ally of [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] whose alliance known as [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|NDA]] formed the [[Government of Assam]] in 2016, it is also a member of the regional alliance of [[North East Democratic Alliance]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Gogoi|first=Tarun|date=2019-06-01|title=North East Democratic Alliance (NEDA) and Political Change in Northeast India|url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/338558276_North_East_Democratic_Alliance_NEDA_and_Political_Change_in_Northeast_India}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n== History ==\n\nThe BPF was formed as political party in year 2005<ref>[http://ceoassam.nic.in/election/AE2016/StarCampainer/Bodoland%20Peoples%20fonrt.pdf BPF Letter head indicating date of foundation</ref>, [[Hagrama Mohilary]] and Emmanuel Mosahary were selected as the President and the General Secretary of the new party. [[Hagrama Mohilary]] formed the first Elected Executive Bodoland Territorial Council after the end of the election. <ref>[https://www.academia.edu/38706042/BODOLAND_PEOPLES_FRONT-_ITS_NATURE_AND_ROLE_-_AN_ANALYTICAL_STUDY BODOLAND PEOPLES FRONT- ITS NATURE AND ROLE </ref><ref>[http://ijmr.net.in/download.php?filename=2017/July,-2017/SPKbbzYkGBjYdLK.pdf&new=IJMSS29July17-6696.pdf BJadav Ch. Basumatary Research Scholar, Bodoland University Dr. Jyotiraj Pathak Deptt. of Political Science, Bodoland University</ref><blockquote>Bodoland Peoples Front formed as per the resolution Vide No. 3, adopted in the Political convention held on 4th and 5th December 2005, as per BPF constitution<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/|title=BPF-Membership Registration System|website=www.bpfonline.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>, BPF shall bear true faith and allegiance to the constitution of India as established by law and to the principles of democracy, socialism and secularism as enshrined in the Indian Constitution, and also solemnly affirm our commitment to work for upholding the sovereignty, unity and integrity of India.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411202907/http://www.bpfassam.in/images/BPF%20Constitution_modify.pdf|title=Wayback Machine|date=2014-04-11|website=web.archive.org|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/|title=BPF-Membership Registration System|website=www.bpfonline.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>To work for strengthening the Indian Nationalism providing due respect to the identities of all sections of people.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bpfonline.in/#ideo|title=BPF-Membership Registration System|website=www.bpfonline.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref></blockquote>\n\n== Flag ==\nBPF flag is tri-colour with 3:2 size and having same significance as follows and Nangal in the middle of white colour.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.relections.in/political-parties/bodoland-peoples-front.php#aboutparty|title=Bodoland People's Front, Bodoland People's Front News, Bodoland People's Front Lok Sabha Elections 2014 News|website=www.relections.in|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n== Lok Sabha Election ==\nIn the [[2009 Indian general election|2009 general election]] its candidate, [[Sansuma Khunggur Bwiswmuthiary]] was elected to the 15th [[Lok Sabha]] from [[Kokrajhar (Lok Sabha constituency)|Kokrajhar]] constituency. [[Biswajit Daimary]] of this party was elected to the [[Rajya Sabha]] in May 2008. BPF had 10 members in the 12th [[Assam Legislative Assembly]] <ref>[https://www.hindustantimes.com/india/assam-polls-cong-sure-test-for-minority-party/story-Y77RSJdaaFCbd0oftLLC0I.html Assam polls: Cong sure, test for minority party]</ref>\n\n==Assembly election==\n\nIn the [[2011 Assam Legislative Assembly election|2011 Assam Assembly election]], BPF won 12 seats.In 2011, with 12 elected lawmakers, the BPF initially supported the [[Indian National Congress|Congress]] government, primarily because of the efforts of [[Himanta Biswa Sarma]], the former minister in the [[Tarun Gogoi]] government who later joined the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]].\n\nThe announcement was made on 19 January when Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] visits [[Kokrajhar]] headquarters of the autonomous [[Bodoland Territorial Council]] and announces a possible economic package of Rs 1000cr or the [[Bodoland Territorial Council]] area.<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/guwahati/BJP-forms-alliance-with-Bodoland-Peoples-Front-for-Assam-elections/articleshow/50617318.cms BJP forms alliance with Bodoland Peoples\u2019 Front for Assam elections]</ref>\n\nWith Assam heading for elections in 2016, [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] made its first alliance with the Bodoland People's Front in [[lower Assam]].In the [[2016 Assam Legislative Assembly election|2016 Assembly Elections]], the BPF won 12 seats and the alliance was established after [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] led [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]] which also includes [[Asom Gana Parishad]] formed its first government in [[Assam]] with [[Pramila Rani Brahma]] and [[Rihon Daimary]] sworn in as ministers in the [[Sarbananda Sonowal ministry (2016\u2013)|Sarbananda Sonowal ministry]]. Later during the cabinet expansion Shri [[Chandan Brahma]] was inducted as Cabinet minister for Tourism and other departments.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sentinelassam.com/north-east-india-news/assam-news/state-tourism-minister-chandan-brahma-inaugurates-community-hall-in-chirang/|title=State Tourism Minister Chandan Brahma inaugurates community hall in Chirang|date=2020-02-04|website=The Sentinel|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\n==North-East Democratic Alliance==\n\nIn May 2016, after the [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] led [[National Democratic Alliance (India)|National Democratic Alliance]] formed its first government in [[Assam]], and formed a new alliance called the [[North-East Democratic Alliance]] (NEDA) with Himanta Biswa Sarma as its [[convener]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/himanta-biswa-sarma-named-convener-of-bjps-northeast-alliance-1409767|title=Himanta Biswa Sarma Named Convener Of BJP's Northeast Alliance|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref> The Chief Ministers of the north eastern states of [[Sikkim]], [[Assam]] and [[Nagaland]] too belong to this alliance.<ref>http://www.hindustantimes.com/india/amit-shah-holds-meeting-with-northeast-cms-forms-alliance/story-YDYLQ6YsImuzZOQ6Zev5MO.html</ref>\n\n== Development in BTC ==\n\n=== Educational Institutions ===\n* Kokrajhar University, Kokrajhar\n\n* [[Central Institute of Technology, Kokrajhar]]\n\n* B.B. Engineering College, Chandrapara, Kokrajhar\n\n* Medical College, Besorgaon, Kokrajhar\n\n* Nursing College, Kokrajhar\n\nBTC chief Hagrama Mohilary laid the foundation stone of Udalguri Engineering College.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/foundation-stones-of-3-institutions-laid-colleges-at-kokrajhar-and-udalguri/cid/430568|title=Foundation stones of 3 institutions laid - Colleges at Kokrajhar and Udalguri|website=www.telegraphindia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\nBTC chief Hagrama Mohilary  laid the foundation stone of a Rs 26-crore IT park at Onthai Gwlao, Chandamari, nearly 4km northwest of Kokrajhar town.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/states/north-east/foundationlaid-for-rs-26-crore-it-park/cid/429920|title=Foundationlaid for Rs 26-crore IT park|website=www.telegraphindia.com|language=en|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n\n* [[Bodo Liberation Tigers Force]]\n* [[Bodo People's Progressive Front]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{India separatist movements}}\n{{Indian political parties}}\n{{North-East Democratic Alliance}}\n{{National Democratic Alliance |state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Political parties in India]]\n[[Category:State political parties in Assam]]\n[[Category:Bodoland]]\n[[Category:Political parties in Assam]]\n[[Category:Recognised state political parties in India]]\n[[Category:Political parties established in 1985]]\n[[Category:1985 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Bodoland People's Front]]\n", "name_user": "Tayi Arajakate", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bodoland_People%27s_Front"}
{"title_page": "Descendants 3", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Disney Channel Original Movie directed by Kenny Ortega}}\n{{Use mdy dates|cs1-dates=ly|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Descendants 3\n| image                    = Descendants 3, poster.jpg\n| image_size               = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = Promotional poster\n| genre                    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Musical film|Musical]]\n* [[Fantasy film|Fantasy]]\n* [[Teen film|Teen]]\n}}\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| writer                   = {{plainlist|\n* [[Josann McGibbon]]\n* [[Sara Parriott]]\n}}\n| screenplay               = \n| story                    = \n| director                 = [[Kenny Ortega]]\n| starring                 = {{plainlist|\n* [[Dove Cameron]]\n* [[Cameron Boyce]]\n* [[Sofia Carson]]\n* [[Booboo Stewart]]\n* [[Cheyenne Jackson]]\n* [[China Anne McClain]]\n<!-- Note: Do not list others as they are not in the poster art. -->\n}}\n| narrated                 = \n| composer                 = [[David Lawrence (composer)|David Lawrence]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_episodes             = \n| executive_producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Kenny Ortega\n* Josann McGibbon\n* Sara Parriott\n* Wendy Japhet\n}}\n| producer                 = Wendy Japhet\n| editor                   = \n| cinematography           = \n| runtime                  = 108 minutes\n| company                  = Disney Channel Original Productions\n| distributor              = \n| budget                   = \n| network                  = [[Disney Channel]]\n| released                 = {{Start date|2019|8|2}}\n| preceded_by              = ''[[Descendants 2]]''\n| followed_by              = \n| website                  = \n}}\n\n'''''Descendants 3''''' is an American [[Musical film|musical]] [[fantasy]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/07/23/descendants-3-review-disney-dove-sofia-carson-cameron-dove-booboo-stewart/|title=Review: 'Descendants 3' Is Both A Satisfying Finale And The End Of An Era|author=Scott Mendelson|website=Forbes|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/06/17/disney-descendants-3-trailer/|title=First trailer for 'Descendants 3' has pirates, dragons, and really great hair|website=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> [[television film]], which is the third<!-- per discussion on talk page, please do not add the words \"and final\" here --> installment in the [[Descendants (franchise)|''Descendants'' series]], following ''[[Descendants (2015 film)|Descendants]]'' and ''[[Descendants 2]]''. It is written by [[Sara Parriott]] and [[Josann McGibbon]], and is directed by [[Kenny Ortega]]. The film premiered on [[Disney Channel]] on August 2, 2019, and in other parts of the world on October 12, 2019.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Please see WP: FILM PLOT before editing. Per key guidelines, the plot summary should be within the desired length of 400-700 words. -->\nMal, Evie, Jay, and Carlos visit the Isle of the Lost to choose four new villain's kids (VKs) to take to Auradon. They pick Dizzy, daughter of Drizella and granddaughter of Lady Tremaine, Celia, daughter of Dr. Facilier, and Squeaky and Squirmy, the twin sons of Mr. Smee. The day the kids are to be picked up, Ben, Mal's boyfriend and the king of Auradon, proposes to her. She accepts; Ben's ex-girlfriend Audrey seethes with jealousy and her grandmother Queen Leah admonishes her for failing to secure the family legacy by marrying Ben.\n\nWhen the barrier is opened for the new VKs, Hades, the god of the underworld, attempts to escape, but Mal beats him back in her dragon form. That night, unable to contain her jealousy of Mal, Audrey steals the Queen's Crown and Maleficent's Scepter from The Museum of Cultural History. The theft and Hades' escape attempt has the citizens panicking. Mal, as future Queen, decides the best way to protect the subjects and restore peace is to close the barrier permanently, meaning no new VKs can come, nor can anyone enter the Isle.\n\nAudrey attacks Mal with Maleficent's scepter, turning her into an old hag. Mal and the other VKs go to the Isle to get Hades' ember, the only thing powerful enough to break the scepter's curse. Mal is restored upon entering the Isle due to the suppression of evil magic there. Celia gets Mal into Hades' lair, but he thwarts their effort to steal the ember. He is revealed to be Mal's absentee father and reluctantly gives her the ember, warning her that it mustn't get wet and will not exhibit its full powers for her. While leaving the Isle, Mal and the others are stopped by Uma, Gil, and Harry, who take the Ember; they agree to help after Mal agrees to release all the children from the Isle.\n\nIn Auradon, Audrey attacks Jane's birthday party with a sleeping curse; Chad obsequiously aligns himself with Audrey, while Jane escapes into the Enchanted Lake. As the entire kingdom falls under Audrey's spell, she offers to reverse it if Ben will marry her; he refuses, so she turns him into a beast and begins turning people to stone. Mal and Uma, vying for leadership of the VKs, return to Auradon with their friends. Despite their bickering, they defeat suits of armor animated by Audrey. Uma finds Audrey's diary and learns that she spends time at Fairy Cottage, a contribution for which Mal thanks her. Evie, nervous to define her feelings for Doug, wakes him with \"true love's kiss.\" Carlos calms Ben, in beast form, until Jane restores him with lake water. As Mal and Uma are thawing towards each other, Audrey traps them in Evie's house; they reverse Audrey's spell by combining their magic, and they all reunite there.\n\nAt the Fairy Cottage, they find only a shell-shocked Chad. When Mal admits that she plans to seal off the Isle permanently, the group implodes and Celia, learning she can never see her father again, throws the ember in a birdbath and Uma and Harry leave. After Evie tells Mal how upset she is for lying to her and their friends, they are all suddenly turned to stone, except for Mal. Audrey takes Celia hostage and attacks Mal, who turns into her dragon form. Realizing she is Mal's only hope, Uma combines their magic to reignite the ember; Mal overcomes Audrey, who falls comatose, and the curses are lifted. The ember could revive Audrey, but only in Hades' hands; Ben agrees to send for him, while Uma, Harry, Gil, and Celia plan to return to the Isle. Mal apologizes for lying; her friends and former rivals forgive her as they understood that she was just trying to do the right thing. Hades arrives and revives Audrey, but decries the double standard by which Audrey is immediately forgiven because she is not considered a villain. Mal and Ben apologize to Audrey; in response, Audrey and Queen Leah apologize to Mal.\n\nMal announces that she cannot be the Queen of Auradon unless she can also be the Queen of the Isle because everyone is capable of being good and bad. With Ben and the Fairy Godmother's agreement, Mal removes the barrier and creates a bridge, and the people of the newly merged society celebrate. Also, Jane and Carlos become official, Mal and Ben are engaged, and Audrey has eyes for Harry (after Uma rejects him).\n\nIn the [[mid-credits scene]], Mal, Evie, Jay, and Carlos are seen looking at the Isle of the Lost; then racing across the bridge to their parents.\n\n==Cast==\n<!-- Note: Cast listed in the same order as in the first two films, which is presumed to be the listed order for this film -->\n* [[Dove Cameron]] as Mal, daughter of [[Maleficent]], and later revealed also to be the daughter of Hades<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* [[Cameron Boyce]] as Carlos, son of [[Cruella de Vil]]<ref name=\"Variety\" /><!--See talk page regarding Boyce's death.-->\n* [[Sofia Carson]] as Evie, daughter of [[Evil Queen (Disney)|The Evil Queen]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* [[Booboo Stewart]] as Jay, son of [[Jafar (Disney)|Jafar]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n*[[China Anne McClain]] as Uma, daughter of [[Ursula (Disney)|Ursula]]\n* Mitchell Hope as Ben, son of [[Belle (Disney)|Belle]] and [[Beast (Disney)|Beast]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* [[Sarah Jeffery]] as Princess Audrey, daughter of [[Aurora (Disney character)|Princess Aurora]] and [[Prince Phillip (Disney)|Prince Phillip]]<ref name=\"Jeffery\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/descendants-3-sarah-jeffery-thomas-doherty-dylan-playfair-reprise-roles-1202372916/|title='Descendants 3': Sarah Jeffery, Thomas Doherty & Dylan Playfair To Reprise Roles In Threequel|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Denise Petski|date=April 20, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n* Brenna D'Amico as Jane, daughter of the Fairy Godmother<ref name=\"E!\" />\n* [[Melanie Paxson]] as [[Fairy Godmother (Disney)|the Fairy Godmother]], the headmistress of Auradon Prep and Jane's mother<ref name=\"Hades2\" />\n* [[Thomas Doherty (actor)|Thomas Doherty]] as Harry Hook, son of [[Captain Hook (Disney)|Captain Hook]] and ally of Uma<ref name=\"Jeffery\" />\n* Dylan Playfair as Gil, son of [[Gaston (Disney)|Gaston]] and ally of Uma<ref name=\"Jeffery\" />\n* Zachary Gibson as Doug, son of [[Dopey (Disney)|Dopey]] the [[Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs|Dwarf]]<ref name=\"E!\" />\n* Jedidiah Goodacre as Chad Charming, son of [[Cinderella (Disney character)|Cinderella]] and [[Prince Charming]]<ref name=\"E!\" />\n* [[Anna Cathcart]] as Dizzy Tremaine, daughter of [[Drizella Tremaine]] and granddaughter of Lady Tremaine<ref name=\"Facilier2\">{{cite web|author=Maureen Lee Lenker|url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/05/04/descendants-3-cast-princess-and-the-frog-dr-facilier-daughter/|title=''Descendants 3'' casts The Princess and the Frog's Dr. Facilier and his daughter|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 4, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n* Jadah Marie as Celia, the daughter of Dr. Facilier<ref name=\"Facilier2\" /><ref name=\"Facilier\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/tv-news-roundup-youtube-red-dallas-robo-1202799856/|title=TV News Roundup: 'Descendants 3' Adds Two More to Cast|work=Variety|author=Ariana Brockington|date=May 4, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n* [[Dan Payne]] as King [[Beast (Disney)|Beast]], Queen Belle's husband and Ben's father<ref name=\"Hades2\" />\n* [[Keegan Connor Tracy]] as Queen [[Belle (Disney)|Belle]], Beast's wife and Ben's mother<ref name=\"Hades2\" />\n* [[Bobby Moynihan]] as the Voice of Dude, Carlos' dog who gained the power of speech in ''[[Descendants 2]]''\n<!-- With -->\n* <!-- And -->[[Cheyenne Jackson]] as [[Hades (Disney)|Hades]], ruler of the underworld and later revealed to be Mal's father<ref name=\"Hades2\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/descendants-3-cheyenne-jackson-hades-disney-channel-hercules-villain-1202395347/|title='Descendants 3': Disney Channel Pic Adds Cheyenne Jackson As Hades From 'Hercules'|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Erik Pedersen|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref><ref name=\"Hades\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/descendants-3-cheyenne-jackson-1202817717/|title=TV News Roundup: 'Descendants 3' Casts Cheyenne Jackson as Hades|work=Variety|author=Kirsten Chuba|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref>\n<!-- End of main end-credits -->\n\nAdditionally, Judith Maxie reprises her role as [[Queen Leah]], Princess Audrey's grandmother, from the first ''Descendants'' film.<ref name=\"casting-tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=descendants|number=998609560956030976|title=Casting is complete! Are you ready for #Descendants3? #D3Deets|date=May 21, 2018|access-date=May 28, 2018}}</ref> Christian Convery and Luke Roessler play Squeaky and Squirmy, respectively, the twin sons of Mr. Smee.<ref name=\"Hades2\" /><ref name=\"casting-tweet\" /> Also appearing are Jamal Sims as Celia's father [[Dr. Facilier]],<ref name=\"Facilier2\" /><ref name=\"Facilier\" /> Linda Ko as Dizzy's grandmother [[Lady Tremaine]], and Faustino Di Bauda as Squeaky's and Squirmy's father [[Mr. Smee]].\n\n== Production ==\nOn February 16, 2018, Disney Channel announced the production of ''Descendants 3'', which Disney scheduled to air in mid-2019.<ref>{{cite web |author=Derek Lawrence |url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/02/16/disney-channel-descendants-3/ |title=Disney Channel officially announces ''Descendants 3'' |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=February 16, 2018 |access-date=February 16, 2018}}</ref> ''Descendants 3'' is written and produced by [[Sara Parriott]] and [[Josann McGibbon]], and is directed and executive produced by [[Kenny Ortega]].<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/disney-announces-descendants-3-1202703195/|title=Disney Announces 'Descendants 3' for 2019|work=Variety|author=Ariana Brockington|date=February 16, 2018|accessdate=2018-02-17}}</ref> Wendy Japhet is a producer on the film,<ref name=\"E!\" /> with Ortega, [[Sara Parriott]], [[Josann McGibbon]], and Japhet also serving as executive producers.<ref name=\"Hades2\" /> Mark Hofeling and Kara Saun return as production designer and costume designer on the sequel, respectively.<ref name=\"E!\" /> In addition to playing Dr. Facilier, Jamal Sims also serves as the film's choreographer,<ref name=\"Facilier2\" /><ref name=\"Facilier\" /> along with Ortega who has served as choreographer for all three ''Descendants'' films.<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n\nRehearsals and pre-recording on the film began on April 23, 2018, in [[Vancouver]], British Columbia, Canada.<ref name=\"E!\">{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/929546/dove-cameron-and-sofia-carson-share-descendants-3-rehearsal-photos|title=Dove Cameron and Sofia Carson Share ''Descendants 3'' Rehearsal Photos|author=Zach Johnson|date=April 24, 2018|work=E! News|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref> Production began on May 25, 2018.<ref name=\"production-tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=descendants|number=1000104379440160768|title=Production has officially begun on #Descendants3! Here's a look back at the behind-the-scenes at this movie's dance rehearsals and voice records leading up to this moment. #D3Deets|date=May 25, 2018|access-date=May 30, 2018}}</ref> On July 18, 2018, it was reported on social media that production on the film had \"officially wrapped\".<ref name=\"instagram-post\">{{cite web|author=disneydescendants|title=Production has officially wrapped on #descendants3|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BlWlg5mD4hX/|date=July 18, 2018|access-date=2018-07-18}}</ref>\n\nIt has been reported that this will be the last film in the ''Descendants'' film series.<ref name=\"Teen-Vogue\">{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/dove-cameron-has-recorded-her-final-descendants-song|title=Dove Cameron Has Recorded Her Final ''Descendants'' Song|author=Brianna Wiest|date=May 18, 2018|work=Teen Vogue|accessdate=2018-05-19|quote=Dove Cameron... recorded her last song EVER for ''Descendants 3'', the third and final movie in the series.}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nSome promotional footage for the film was released on the Disney Descendants [[YouTube]] channel in February 2018 as a teaser or first look into the production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_0ovuLsnU1A|title=Descendants 3 Official Teaser \ud83d\udc9a\ud83d\udc9c|author=Disney Descendants|date=February 16, 2018|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> In late May 2019, it was announced that the film would premiere on August 2, 2019.<ref name=\"premiere\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/descendants-3-premiere-date-disney-channel-1202624719/|title=''Descendants 3'' Gets Premiere Date on Disney Channel|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Erik Pedersen|date=May 31, 2019|access-date=May 31, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1036123/hades-is-pretty-mad-in-first-look-at-cheyenne-jackson-s-new-descendants-3-villain|title=Hades Is Pretty Mad in First Look at Cheyenne Jackson's New Descendants 3 Villain|website=EOnline.com|author=Lauren Piester|date=April 27, 2019|accessdate=April 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA related short film, ''Under the Sea: A Descendants Short Story'', which features Mal and Uma facing off in \"an epic underwater showdown\", was released on September 28, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |author=Zach Johnson |url=https://m.eonline.com/news/959479/under-the-sea-a-descendants-story-coming-to-disney-channel |title=''Under the Sea: A Descendants Story'' Special Coming to Disney Channel |work=E! News |date=August 10, 2018 |access-date=2018-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Crystal Nguyen |url=https://ohmy.disney.com/news/2018/09/07/under-the-sea-a-descendants-short-story-trailer/ |title=A New Trailer for \"Under the Sea: A Descendants Short Story\" Has Been Released and We Can\u2019t Wait |work=Oh My Disney |date=September 7, 2018 |access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref>\n\nOn July 11, 2019, Disney announced it was canceling a red carpet premiere originally planned for July 22, 2019, in the wake of Cameron Boyce's death. The film's television premiere went on as scheduled, dedicated to Boyce's memory.<ref name=\"Boyce\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-cancels-descendants-3-premiere-event-honor-star-cameron-boyce-1223972|title=Disney Cancels 'Descendants 3' Premiere Event in Wake of Cameron Boyce's Death|author=Lexy Perez|work=They Hollywood Reporter|date=July 11, 2019|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref><!--Please do not remove this.-->\n\n==Reception==\n''Descendants 3'' was watched by 4.59 million viewers on its August 2, 2019 premiere,<ref name=\"Showbuzz Daily\">{{cite web |author=Mitch Metcalf  |title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 8.2.2019 |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-8-2-2019.html |website=Showbuzz Daily |date=August 5, 2019 |access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> with viewership increasing to 8.43 million viewers after three days of delayed viewing.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/descendants-3-scores-big-ratings-disney-channel-1230053 |title = 'Descendants 3' Scores Big Ratings for Disney Channel |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=August 7, 2019 |accessdate=August 15, 2019 |first=Rick |last=Porter}}</ref> The film currently has a 78% approval rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] based on 9 reviews.<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/descendants_3</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Descendants 3<br/>(Original TV Movie Soundtrack)\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = ''[[Descendants (franchise)|Descendants]]'' cast\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = August 2, 2019\n| recorded     = April\u2014May 2018\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| producer     = \n| chronology   = ''[[Descendants (franchise)|Descendants]]'' soundtracks\n| prev_title   = [[Descendants 2 (soundtrack)|Descendants 2]]\n| prev_year    = 2017\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Descendants 3\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = Good to Be Bad\n | single1date = May 31, 2019\n | single2     = VK Mashup\n | single2date = July 19, 2019\n | single3     = [[Queen of Mean (song)|Queen of Mean]]\n | single3date = August 2, 2019\n}}\n}}\n'''''Descendants 3 (Original TV Movie Soundtrack)''''' is the [[soundtrack]] accompanying the film of the same name. The soundtrack and lead single, \"Good to Be Bad\", was released on May 31, 2019, along with the pre-order of the soundtrack. The soundtrack was released on August 2, 2019. It reached number 7 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] album chart,<ref name=\"billboard200\"/> and number 1 on the [[Billboard Kid Albums|''Billboard'' Kid Albums]] chart.<ref name=\"kidalbums\">{{cite web |title=Kid Albums week of August 17, 2019 |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/kids-albums |website=Billboard.com |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Descendants 3 (Original TV Movie Soundtrack)'' {{nobold|\u2013 Standard edition}}\n| extra_column = Performer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1 = Good to Be Bad\n| writer1 = {{flatlist|\n*Tim James\n*[[Antonina Armato]]\n*[[Tom Sturges]]\n*Adam Schmalholz\n}}\n| extra1 = {{flatlist|\n*[[Dove Cameron]]\n*[[Sofia Carson]]\n*[[Cameron Boyce]]\n*[[Booboo Stewart]]\n*[[Anna Cathcart]]\n*Jadah Marie\n}}\n| length1 = 3:09\n| title2 = [[Queen of Mean (song)|Queen of Mean]]\n| writer2 = {{flatlist|\n*James\n*Armato\n*Sturges\n*Schmalholz\n}}\n| extra2 = [[Sarah Jeffery]]\n| length2 = 3:09\n| title3 = Do What You Gotta Do\n| writer3 = {{flatlist|\n*Matt Wong\n*Jamie Jones\n*Jack Kugell\n}}\n| extra3 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*[[Cheyenne Jackson]]\n}}\n| length3 = 2:57\n| title4 = Night Falls\n| writer4 = {{flatlist|\n*James\n*Armato\n*Sturges\n*Schmalholz\n}}\n| extra4 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n*[[China Anne McClain]]\n*[[Thomas Doherty (actor)|Thomas Doherty]]\n*Dylan Playfair\n}}\n| length4 = 3:08\n| title5 = One Kiss\n| writer5 = {{flatlist|\n*[[Matthew Tishler|Matt Tishler]]\n*Paula Wingler\n}}\n| extra5 = {{flatlist|\n*Carson\n*Cameron\n*McClain\n}}\n| length5 = 2:29\n| title6 = My Once Upon a Time\n| note6 = \n| writer6 = {{flatlist|\n*[[John Kavanaugh]]\n*[[David Goldsmith (lyricist)|David Goldsmith]]\n}}\n| extra6 = Cameron\n| length6 = 3:48\n| title7 = Break This Down\n| writer7 = {{flatlist|\n*Jodie Shihadeh\n*James K. Petrie\n*Doug Davis\n*Ben Hostetler\n*Nikki Sorrentino\n*Susan Paroff\n*Anthony Mirabella\n*Pipo Fernandez\n*Ali Dee Theodore\n}}\n| extra7 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n*McClain\n*Jeffery\n*Doherty\n*Playfair\n*Cathcart\n*Marie\n*Mitchell Hope\n*Brenna D'Amico\n*Zachary Gibson\n}}\n| length7 = 3:29\n| title8 = Dig a Little Deeper\n| writer8 = [[Randy Newman]]\n| extra8 = McClain\n| length8 = 2:57\n| title9 = Did I Mention\n| writer9 = [[Adam Schlesinger]]\n| extra9 = Hope\n| length9 = 0:29\n| title10 = Rotten to the Core\n| note10 = D3 Remix\n| writer10 = {{flatlist|\n*[[Shelly Peiken]]\n*Johan Alknas\n*Joacim Persson\n}}\n| extra10 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n*McClain\n*Jeffery\n*Doherty\n*Marie\n}}\n| length10 = 2:47\n| title11 = Happy Birthday\n| writer11 = <small>Traditional</small>\n| extra11 = Jeffery\n| length11 = 0:36\n| title12 = VK Mashup\n| writer12 = {{flatlist|\n*James\n*Armato\n*Sturges\n*Schmalholz\n*Pieken\n*Alkenas\n*Persson\n*[[Grant P Michaels]]\n*[[Charity Daw]]\n}}\n| extra12 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n}}\n| length12 = 1:59\n| title13 = ''Descendants 3'' Score Suite\n| writer13 = [[David Lawrence (composer)|David Lawrence]]\n| extra13 = [[David Lawrence (composer)|David Lawrence]]\n| length13 = 5:01\n| all_writing = \n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n* \"VK Mashup\" contains samples of \"[[Rotten to the Core (song)|Rotten to the Core]]\", \"[[Ways to Be Wicked (Descendants song)|Ways to Be Wicked]]\", and \"Good to be Bad\", from the first, second and third soundtracks.\n\n===Chart performance===\nThe album debuted at number 7 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8527130/drake-achieves-ninth-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-chart-with|title=Drake Achieves Ninth No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Care Package'|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref> and in its second week the album dropped to number 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200|title=Top 200 Albums {{!}} Billboard 200 chart|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref>\n\nThe single \"[[Queen of Mean (song)|Queen of Mean]]\" reached number 49 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Sarah Jeffrey Chart History Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Sarah-Jeffrey/chart-history/hot-100 |website=Billboard |accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref> number 57 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Sarah Jeffrey Chart History Canadian Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Sarah-Jeffrey/chart-history/canadian-hot-100 |website=Billboard |accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref> and number 89 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Official Singles Chart Top 100, 16 August 2019 - 22 August 2019 |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20190816/7501/ |website=Official Charts |accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|36|artist=Soundtrack|album=Descendants 3|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 10, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|109|artist=Soundtrack|album=Descendants 3|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|36|M|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2019/08/12/charts-august-12-2019|title=On The Charts: August 12, 2019|work=FYIMusicNews|artist=Soundtrack|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|74|artist=Soundtrack|album=Descendants 3|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| French Albums ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-album-megafusion/?ye=2019&we=44|title=Le Top de la semaine : Top Albums Fusionnes \u2013 SNEP (Week 44, 2019)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| 166\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Spanish Albums ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/4222-%C3%81lbumes-semana-45-2019|title=Top 100 Albumes \u2013 Semana 45: del 01.11.2019 al 07.11.2019|publisher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=November 13, 2019}}</ref>\n| 82\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref name=\"billboard200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8527130/drake-achieves-ninth-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-chart-with|title=Drake Achieves Ninth No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Care Package'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=August 11, 2019|accessdate=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Kid Albums]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/kids-albums/2019-08-17|title=Soundtrack albums \u2013 August 17, 2017|work=Billboard|date=August 17, 2017 |accessdate=August 13, 2017}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Soundtrack Albums ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/soundtracks/2019-08-17|title=Soundtrack albums \u2013 August 17, 2017|work=Billboard|date=August 17, 2017 |accessdate=August 13, 2017}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 200|''Rolling Stone'' Top 200]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/albums/2019-08-02/|title=Top 200 Albums|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=March 1, 2020}}</ref>\n| 13\n|}\n\n== Home media ==\n''Descendants 3'' was released on [[DVD]] on August 6, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://amazonadviser.com/2019/07/18/disneys-descendants-3-dvd-august/|title=Disney\u2019s Descendants 3 comes home in August 2019|date=July 18, 2019|website=Amazon Adviser|access-date=2019-07-21}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|8022928}}\n\n{{Descendants franchise}}\n{{Disney Channel Original Movies}}\n{{Kenny Ortega}}\n\n[[Category:2010s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:2019 television films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:Crossover films]]\n[[Category:Descendants (franchise)]]\n[[Category:Disney Channel Original Movie films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Kenny Ortega]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Vancouver]]\n[[Category:Television sequel films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Disney Channel Original Movie directed by Kenny Ortega}}\n{{Use mdy dates|cs1-dates=ly|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Descendants 3\n| image                    = Descendants 3, poster.jpg\n| image_size               = \n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = Promotional poster\n| genre                    = {{plainlist|\n* [[Musical film|Musical]]\n* [[Fantasy film|Fantasy]]\n* [[Teen film|Teen]]\n}}\n| creator                  = \n| based_on                 = \n| writer                   = {{plainlist|\n* [[Josann McGibbon]]\n* [[Sara Parriott]]\n}}\n| screenplay               = \n| story                    = \n| director                 = [[Kenny Ortega]]\n| starring                 = {{plainlist|\n* [[Dove Cameron]]\n* [[Cameron Boyce]]\n* [[Sofia Carson]]\n* [[Booboo Stewart]]\n* [[Cheyenne Jackson]]\n* [[China Anne McClain]]\n<!-- Note: Do not list others as they are not in the poster art. -->\n}}\n| narrated                 = \n| composer                 = [[David Lawrence (composer)|David Lawrence]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| num_episodes             = \n| executive_producer       = {{plainlist|\n* Kenny Ortega\n* Josann McGibbon\n* Sara Parriott\n* Wendy Japhet\n}}\n| producer                 = Wendy Japhet\n| editor                   = \n| cinematography           = \n| runtime                  = 108 minutes\n| company                  = Disney Channel Original Productions\n| distributor              = \n| budget                   = \n| network                  = [[Disney Channel]]\n| released                 = {{Start date|2019|8|2}}\n| preceded_by              = ''[[Descendants 2]]''\n| followed_by              = \n| website                  = \n}}\n\n'''''Descendants 3''''' is an American [[Musical film|musical]] [[fantasy]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/scottmendelson/2019/07/23/descendants-3-review-disney-dove-sofia-carson-cameron-dove-booboo-stewart/|title=Review: 'Descendants 3' Is Both A Satisfying Finale And The End Of An Era|author=Scott Mendelson|website=Forbes|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/tv/2019/06/17/disney-descendants-3-trailer/|title=First trailer for 'Descendants 3' has pirates, dragons, and really great hair|website=Entertainment Weekly|access-date=2019-08-05}}</ref> [[television film]], which is the third<!-- per discussion on talk page, please do not add the words \"and final\" here --> installment in the [[Descendants (franchise)|''Descendants'' series]], following ''[[Descendants (2015 film)|Descendants]]'' and ''[[Descendants 2]]''. It is written by [[Sara Parriott]] and [[Josann McGibbon]], and is directed by [[Kenny Ortega]]. The film premiered on [[Disney Channel]] on August 2, 2019, and in other parts of the world on October 12, 2019.\n\n==Plot==\n<!-- Please see WP: FILM PLOT before editing. Per key guidelines, the plot summary should be within the desired length of 400-700 words. -->\nMal, Evie, Jay, and Carlos visit the Isle of the Lost to choose four new villain's kids (VKs) to take to Auradon. They pick Dizzy, daughter of Drizella and granddaughter of Lady Tremaine, Celia, daughter of Dr. Facilier, and Squeaky and Squirmy, the twin sons of Mr. Smee. The day the kids are to be picked up, Ben, Mal's boyfriend and the king of Auradon, proposes to her. She accepts; Ben's ex-girlfriend Audrey seethes with jealousy and her grandmother Queen Leah admonishes her for failing to secure the family legacy by marrying Ben.\n\nWhen the barrier is opened for the new VKs, Hades, the god of the underworld, attempts to escape, but Mal beats him back in her dragon form. That night, unable to contain her jealousy of Mal, Audrey steals the Queen's Crown and Maleficent's Scepter from The Museum of Cultural History. The theft and Hades' escape attempt has the citizens panicking. Mal, as future Queen, decides the best way to protect the subjects and restore peace is to close the barrier permanently, meaning no new VKs can come, nor can anyone enter the Isle.\n\nAudrey attacks Mal with Maleficent's scepter, turning her into an old hag. Mal and the other VKs go to the Isle to get Hades' ember, the only thing powerful enough to break the scepter's curse. Mal is restored upon entering the Isle due to the suppression of evil magic there. Celia gets Mal into Hades' lair, but he thwarts their effort to steal the ember. He is revealed to be Mal's absentee father and reluctantly gives her the ember, warning her that it mustn't get wet and will not exhibit its full powers for her. While leaving the Isle, Mal and the others are stopped by Uma, Gil, and Harry, who take the Ember; they agree to help after Mal agrees to release all the children from the Isle.\n\nIn Auradon, Audrey attacks Jane's birthday party with a sleeping curse; Chad obsequiously aligns himself with Audrey, while Jane escapes into the Enchanted Lake. As the entire kingdom falls under Audrey's spell, she offers to reverse it if Ben will marry her; he refuses, so she turns him into a beast and begins turning people to stone. Mal and Uma, vying for leadership of the VKs, return to Auradon with their friends. Despite their bickering, they defeat suits of armor animated by Audrey. Uma finds Audrey's diary and learns that she spends time at Fairy Cottage, a contribution for which Mal thanks her. Evie, nervous to define her feelings for Doug, wakes him with \"true love's kiss.\" Carlos calms Ben, in beast form, until Jane restores him with lake water. As Mal and Uma are thawing towards each other, Audrey traps them in Evie's house; they reverse Audrey's spell by combining their magic, and they all reunite there.\n\nAt the Fairy Cottage, they find only a shell-shocked Chad. When Mal admits that she plans to seal off the Isle permanently, the group implodes and Celia, learning she can never see her father again, throws the ember in a birdbath and Uma and Harry leave. After Evie tells Mal how upset she is for lying to her and their friends, they are all suddenly turned to stone, except for Mal. Audrey takes Celia hostage and attacks Mal, who turns into her dragon form. Realizing she is Mal's only hope, Uma combines their magic to reignite the ember; Mal overcomes Audrey, who falls comatose, and the curses are lifted. The ember could revive Audrey, but only in Hades' hands; Ben agrees to send for him, while Uma, Harry, Gil, and Celia plan to return to the Isle. Mal apologizes for lying; her friends and former rivals forgive her as they understood that she was just trying to do the right thing. Hades arrives and revives Audrey, but decries the double standard by which Audrey is immediately forgiven because she is not considered a villain. Mal and Ben apologize to Audrey; in response, Audrey and Queen Leah apologize to Mal.\n\nMal announces that she cannot be the Queen of Auradon unless she can also be the Queen of the Isle because everyone is capable of being good and bad. With Ben and the Fairy Godmother's agreement, Mal removes the barrier and creates a bridge, and the people of the newly merged society celebrate. Also, Jane and Carlos become official, Mal and Ben are engaged, and Audrey has eyes for Harry (after Uma rejects him).\n\nIn the [[mid-credits scene]], Mal, Evie, Jay, and Carlos are seen looking at the Isle of the Lost; then racing across the bridge to their parents.\n\n==Cast==\n<!-- Note: Cast listed in the same order as in the first two films, which is presumed to be the listed order for this film -->\n* [[Dove Cameron]] as Mal, daughter of [[Maleficent]], and later revealed also to be the daughter of Hades<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* [[Cameron Boyce]] as Carlos, son of [[Cruella de Vil]]<ref name=\"Variety\" /><!--See talk page regarding Boyce's death.-->\n* [[Sofia Carson]] as Evie, daughter of [[Evil Queen (Disney)|The Evil Queen]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* [[Booboo Stewart]] as Jay, son of [[Jafar (Disney)|Jafar]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* Mitchell Hope as Ben, son of [[Belle (Disney)|Belle]] and [[Beast (Disney)|Beast]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n* [[Sarah Jeffery]] as Princess Audrey, daughter of [[Aurora (Disney character)|Princess Aurora]] and [[Prince Phillip (Disney)|Prince Phillip]]<ref name=\"Jeffery\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/04/descendants-3-sarah-jeffery-thomas-doherty-dylan-playfair-reprise-roles-1202372916/|title='Descendants 3': Sarah Jeffery, Thomas Doherty & Dylan Playfair To Reprise Roles In Threequel|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Denise Petski|date=April 20, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n* Brenna D'Amico as Jane, daughter of the Fairy Godmother<ref name=\"E!\" />\n* [[Melanie Paxson]] as [[Fairy Godmother (Disney)|the Fairy Godmother]], the headmistress of Auradon Prep and Jane's mother<ref name=\"Hades2\" />\n* [[Thomas Doherty (actor)|Thomas Doherty]] as Harry Hook, son of [[Captain Hook (Disney)|Captain Hook]] and ally of Uma<ref name=\"Jeffery\" />\n* Dylan Playfair as Gil, son of [[Gaston (Disney)|Gaston]] and ally of Uma<ref name=\"Jeffery\" />\n* Zachary Gibson as Doug, son of [[Dopey (Disney)|Dopey]] the [[Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs|Dwarf]]<ref name=\"E!\" />\n* Jedidiah Goodacre as Chad Charming, son of [[Cinderella (Disney character)|Cinderella]] and [[Prince Charming]]<ref name=\"E!\" />\n* [[Anna Cathcart]] as Dizzy Tremaine, daughter of [[Drizella Tremaine]] and granddaughter of Lady Tremaine<ref name=\"Facilier2\">{{cite web|author=Maureen Lee Lenker|url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/05/04/descendants-3-cast-princess-and-the-frog-dr-facilier-daughter/|title=''Descendants 3'' casts The Princess and the Frog's Dr. Facilier and his daughter|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=May 4, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n* Jadah Marie as Celia, the daughter of Dr. Facilier<ref name=\"Facilier2\" /><ref name=\"Facilier\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/tv-news-roundup-youtube-red-dallas-robo-1202799856/|title=TV News Roundup: 'Descendants 3' Adds Two More to Cast|work=Variety|author=Ariana Brockington|date=May 4, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref>\n* [[Dan Payne]] as King [[Beast (Disney)|Beast]], Queen Belle's husband and Ben's father<ref name=\"Hades2\" />\n* [[Keegan Connor Tracy]] as Queen [[Belle (Disney)|Belle]], Beast's wife and Ben's mother<ref name=\"Hades2\" />\n* [[Bobby Moynihan]] as the Voice of Dude, Carlos' dog who gained the power of speech in ''[[Descendants 2]]''\n<!-- With -->\n* [[Cheyenne Jackson]] as [[Hades (Disney)|Hades]], ruler of the underworld and later revealed to be Mal's father<ref name=\"Hades2\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/05/descendants-3-cheyenne-jackson-hades-disney-channel-hercules-villain-1202395347/|title='Descendants 3': Disney Channel Pic Adds Cheyenne Jackson As Hades From 'Hercules'|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Erik Pedersen|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref><ref name=\"Hades\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/descendants-3-cheyenne-jackson-1202817717/|title=TV News Roundup: 'Descendants 3' Casts Cheyenne Jackson as Hades|work=Variety|author=Kirsten Chuba|date=May 21, 2018|accessdate=2018-05-28}}</ref>\n<!-- And -->\n* [[China Anne McClain]] as Uma, daughter of [[Ursula (Disney)|Ursula]]<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n<!-- End of main end-credits -->\n\nAdditionally, Judith Maxie reprises her role as [[Queen Leah]], Princess Audrey's grandmother, from the first ''Descendants'' film.<ref name=\"casting-tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=descendants|number=998609560956030976|title=Casting is complete! Are you ready for #Descendants3? #D3Deets|date=May 21, 2018|access-date=May 28, 2018}}</ref> Christian Convery and Luke Roessler play Squeaky and Squirmy, respectively, the twin sons of Mr. Smee.<ref name=\"Hades2\" /><ref name=\"casting-tweet\" /> Also appearing are Jamal Sims as Celia's father [[Dr. Facilier]],<ref name=\"Facilier2\" /><ref name=\"Facilier\" /> Linda Ko as Dizzy's grandmother [[Lady Tremaine]], and Faustino Di Bauda as Squeaky's and Squirmy's father [[Mr. Smee]].\n\n== Production ==\nOn February 16, 2018, Disney Channel announced the production of ''Descendants 3'', which Disney scheduled to air in mid-2019.<ref>{{cite web |author=Derek Lawrence |url=https://ew.com/tv/2018/02/16/disney-channel-descendants-3/ |title=Disney Channel officially announces ''Descendants 3'' |work=Entertainment Weekly |date=February 16, 2018 |access-date=February 16, 2018}}</ref> ''Descendants 3'' is written and produced by [[Sara Parriott]] and [[Josann McGibbon]], and is directed and executive produced by [[Kenny Ortega]].<ref name=\"Variety\">{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/disney-announces-descendants-3-1202703195/|title=Disney Announces 'Descendants 3' for 2019|work=Variety|author=Ariana Brockington|date=February 16, 2018|accessdate=2018-02-17}}</ref> Wendy Japhet is a producer on the film,<ref name=\"E!\" /> with Ortega, [[Sara Parriott]], [[Josann McGibbon]], and Japhet also serving as executive producers.<ref name=\"Hades2\" /> Mark Hofeling and Kara Saun return as production designer and costume designer on the sequel, respectively.<ref name=\"E!\" /> In addition to playing Dr. Facilier, Jamal Sims also serves as the film's choreographer,<ref name=\"Facilier2\" /><ref name=\"Facilier\" /> along with Ortega who has served as choreographer for all three ''Descendants'' films.<ref name=\"Variety\" />\n\nRehearsals and pre-recording on the film began on April 23, 2018, in [[Vancouver]], British Columbia, Canada.<ref name=\"E!\">{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/929546/dove-cameron-and-sofia-carson-share-descendants-3-rehearsal-photos|title=Dove Cameron and Sofia Carson Share ''Descendants 3'' Rehearsal Photos|author=Zach Johnson|date=April 24, 2018|work=E! News|accessdate=2018-05-05}}</ref> Production began on May 25, 2018.<ref name=\"production-tweet\">{{cite tweet|user=descendants|number=1000104379440160768|title=Production has officially begun on #Descendants3! Here's a look back at the behind-the-scenes at this movie's dance rehearsals and voice records leading up to this moment. #D3Deets|date=May 25, 2018|access-date=May 30, 2018}}</ref> On July 18, 2018, it was reported on social media that production on the film had \"officially wrapped\".<ref name=\"instagram-post\">{{cite web|author=disneydescendants|title=Production has officially wrapped on #descendants3|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BlWlg5mD4hX/|date=July 18, 2018|access-date=2018-07-18}}</ref>\n\nIt has been reported that this will be the last film in the ''Descendants'' film series.<ref name=\"Teen-Vogue\">{{cite web|url=https://www.teenvogue.com/story/dove-cameron-has-recorded-her-final-descendants-song|title=Dove Cameron Has Recorded Her Final ''Descendants'' Song|author=Brianna Wiest|date=May 18, 2018|work=Teen Vogue|accessdate=2018-05-19|quote=Dove Cameron... recorded her last song EVER for ''Descendants 3'', the third and final movie in the series.}}</ref>\n\n== Release ==\nSome promotional footage for the film was released on the Disney Descendants [[YouTube]] channel in February 2018 as a teaser or first look into the production.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_0ovuLsnU1A|title=Descendants 3 Official Teaser \ud83d\udc9a\ud83d\udc9c|author=Disney Descendants|date=February 16, 2018|publisher=|via=YouTube}}</ref> In late May 2019, it was announced that the film would premiere on August 2, 2019.<ref name=\"premiere\">{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2019/05/descendants-3-premiere-date-disney-channel-1202624719/|title=''Descendants 3'' Gets Premiere Date on Disney Channel|work=Deadline Hollywood|author=Erik Pedersen|date=May 31, 2019|access-date=May 31, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"Variety\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1036123/hades-is-pretty-mad-in-first-look-at-cheyenne-jackson-s-new-descendants-3-villain|title=Hades Is Pretty Mad in First Look at Cheyenne Jackson's New Descendants 3 Villain|website=EOnline.com|author=Lauren Piester|date=April 27, 2019|accessdate=April 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nA related short film, ''Under the Sea: A Descendants Short Story'', which features Mal and Uma facing off in \"an epic underwater showdown\", was released on September 28, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |author=Zach Johnson |url=https://m.eonline.com/news/959479/under-the-sea-a-descendants-story-coming-to-disney-channel |title=''Under the Sea: A Descendants Story'' Special Coming to Disney Channel |work=E! News |date=August 10, 2018 |access-date=2018-08-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=Crystal Nguyen |url=https://ohmy.disney.com/news/2018/09/07/under-the-sea-a-descendants-short-story-trailer/ |title=A New Trailer for \"Under the Sea: A Descendants Short Story\" Has Been Released and We Can\u2019t Wait |work=Oh My Disney |date=September 7, 2018 |access-date=2018-09-29}}</ref>\n\nOn July 11, 2019, Disney announced it was canceling a red carpet premiere originally planned for July 22, 2019, in the wake of Cameron Boyce's death. The film's television premiere went on as scheduled, dedicated to Boyce's memory.<ref name=\"Boyce\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/disney-cancels-descendants-3-premiere-event-honor-star-cameron-boyce-1223972|title=Disney Cancels 'Descendants 3' Premiere Event in Wake of Cameron Boyce's Death|author=Lexy Perez|work=They Hollywood Reporter|date=July 11, 2019|access-date=July 11, 2019}}</ref><!--Please do not remove this.-->\n\n==Reception==\n''Descendants 3'' was watched by 4.59 million viewers on its August 2, 2019 premiere,<ref name=\"Showbuzz Daily\">{{cite web |author=Mitch Metcalf  |title=SHOWBUZZDAILY's Top 150 Friday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 8.2.2019 |url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-friday-cable-originals-network-finals-8-2-2019.html |website=Showbuzz Daily |date=August 5, 2019 |access-date=August 5, 2019}}</ref> with viewership increasing to 8.43 million viewers after three days of delayed viewing.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/descendants-3-scores-big-ratings-disney-channel-1230053 |title = 'Descendants 3' Scores Big Ratings for Disney Channel |magazine=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=August 7, 2019 |accessdate=August 15, 2019 |first=Rick |last=Porter}}</ref> The film currently has a 78% approval rating on [[Rotten Tomatoes]] based on 9 reviews.<ref>https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/descendants_3</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Descendants 3<br/>(Original TV Movie Soundtrack)\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = ''[[Descendants (franchise)|Descendants]]'' cast\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = August 2, 2019\n| recorded     = April\u2014May 2018\n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Pop music|Pop]]\n| length       = \n| label        = [[Walt Disney Records|Walt Disney]]\n| producer     = \n| chronology   = ''[[Descendants (franchise)|Descendants]]'' soundtracks\n| prev_title   = [[Descendants 2 (soundtrack)|Descendants 2]]\n| prev_year    = 2017\n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{Singles\n | name        = Descendants 3\n | type        = soundtrack\n | single1     = Good to Be Bad\n | single1date = May 31, 2019\n | single2     = VK Mashup\n | single2date = July 19, 2019\n | single3     = [[Queen of Mean (song)|Queen of Mean]]\n | single3date = August 2, 2019\n}}\n}}\n'''''Descendants 3 (Original TV Movie Soundtrack)''''' is the [[soundtrack]] accompanying the film of the same name. The soundtrack and lead single, \"Good to Be Bad\", was released on May 31, 2019, along with the pre-order of the soundtrack. The soundtrack was released on August 2, 2019. It reached number 7 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] album chart,<ref name=\"billboard200\"/> and number 1 on the [[Billboard Kid Albums|''Billboard'' Kid Albums]] chart.<ref name=\"kidalbums\">{{cite web |title=Kid Albums week of August 17, 2019 |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/kids-albums |website=Billboard.com |accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Track listing===\n{{Track listing\n| headline = ''Descendants 3 (Original TV Movie Soundtrack)'' {{nobold|\u2013 Standard edition}}\n| extra_column = Performer(s)\n| total_length = \n| title1 = Good to Be Bad\n| writer1 = {{flatlist|\n*Tim James\n*[[Antonina Armato]]\n*[[Tom Sturges]]\n*Adam Schmalholz\n}}\n| extra1 = {{flatlist|\n*[[Dove Cameron]]\n*[[Sofia Carson]]\n*[[Cameron Boyce]]\n*[[Booboo Stewart]]\n*[[Anna Cathcart]]\n*Jadah Marie\n}}\n| length1 = 3:09\n| title2 = [[Queen of Mean (song)|Queen of Mean]]\n| writer2 = {{flatlist|\n*James\n*Armato\n*Sturges\n*Schmalholz\n}}\n| extra2 = [[Sarah Jeffery]]\n| length2 = 3:09\n| title3 = Do What You Gotta Do\n| writer3 = {{flatlist|\n*Matt Wong\n*Jamie Jones\n*Jack Kugell\n}}\n| extra3 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*[[Cheyenne Jackson]]\n}}\n| length3 = 2:57\n| title4 = Night Falls\n| writer4 = {{flatlist|\n*James\n*Armato\n*Sturges\n*Schmalholz\n}}\n| extra4 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n*[[China Anne McClain]]\n*[[Thomas Doherty (actor)|Thomas Doherty]]\n*Dylan Playfair\n}}\n| length4 = 3:08\n| title5 = One Kiss\n| writer5 = {{flatlist|\n*[[Matthew Tishler|Matt Tishler]]\n*Paula Wingler\n}}\n| extra5 = {{flatlist|\n*Carson\n*Cameron\n*McClain\n}}\n| length5 = 2:29\n| title6 = My Once Upon a Time\n| note6 = \n| writer6 = {{flatlist|\n*[[John Kavanaugh]]\n*[[David Goldsmith (lyricist)|David Goldsmith]]\n}}\n| extra6 = Cameron\n| length6 = 3:48\n| title7 = Break This Down\n| writer7 = {{flatlist|\n*Jodie Shihadeh\n*James K. Petrie\n*Doug Davis\n*Ben Hostetler\n*Nikki Sorrentino\n*Susan Paroff\n*Anthony Mirabella\n*Pipo Fernandez\n*Ali Dee Theodore\n}}\n| extra7 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n*McClain\n*Jeffery\n*Doherty\n*Playfair\n*Cathcart\n*Marie\n*Mitchell Hope\n*Brenna D'Amico\n*Zachary Gibson\n}}\n| length7 = 3:29\n| title8 = Dig a Little Deeper\n| writer8 = [[Randy Newman]]\n| extra8 = McClain\n| length8 = 2:57\n| title9 = Did I Mention\n| writer9 = [[Adam Schlesinger]]\n| extra9 = Hope\n| length9 = 0:29\n| title10 = Rotten to the Core\n| note10 = D3 Remix\n| writer10 = {{flatlist|\n*[[Shelly Peiken]]\n*Johan Alknas\n*Joacim Persson\n}}\n| extra10 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n*McClain\n*Jeffery\n*Doherty\n*Marie\n}}\n| length10 = 2:47\n| title11 = Happy Birthday\n| writer11 = <small>Traditional</small>\n| extra11 = Jeffery\n| length11 = 0:36\n| title12 = VK Mashup\n| writer12 = {{flatlist|\n*James\n*Armato\n*Sturges\n*Schmalholz\n*Pieken\n*Alkenas\n*Persson\n*[[Grant P Michaels]]\n*[[Charity Daw]]\n}}\n| extra12 = {{flatlist|\n*Cameron\n*Boyce\n*Carson\n*Stewart\n}}\n| length12 = 1:59\n| title13 = ''Descendants 3'' Score Suite\n| writer13 = [[David Lawrence (composer)|David Lawrence]]\n| extra13 = [[David Lawrence (composer)|David Lawrence]]\n| length13 = 5:01\n| all_writing = \n}}\n\n'''Notes'''\n* \"VK Mashup\" contains samples of \"[[Rotten to the Core (song)|Rotten to the Core]]\", \"[[Ways to Be Wicked (Descendants song)|Ways to Be Wicked]]\", and \"Good to be Bad\", from the first, second and third soundtracks.\n\n===Chart performance===\nThe album debuted at number 7 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8527130/drake-achieves-ninth-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-chart-with|title=Drake Achieves Ninth No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Care Package'|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref> and in its second week the album dropped to number 14.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/billboard-200|title=Top 200 Albums {{!}} Billboard 200 chart|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-08-29}}</ref>\n\nThe single \"[[Queen of Mean (song)|Queen of Mean]]\" reached number 49 on the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Sarah Jeffrey Chart History Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Sarah-Jeffrey/chart-history/hot-100 |website=Billboard |accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref> number 57 on the [[Canadian Hot 100]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Sarah Jeffrey Chart History Canadian Hot 100 |url=https://www.billboard.com/music/Sarah-Jeffrey/chart-history/canadian-hot-100 |website=Billboard |accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref> and number 89 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Official Singles Chart Top 100, 16 August 2019 - 22 August 2019 |url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20190816/7501/ |website=Official Charts |accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2019)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|36|artist=Soundtrack|album=Descendants 3|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 10, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|109|artist=Soundtrack|album=Descendants 3|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|36|M|url=https://www.fyimusicnews.ca/articles/2019/08/12/charts-august-12-2019|title=On The Charts: August 12, 2019|work=FYIMusicNews|artist=Soundtrack|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 13, 2019}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|74|artist=Soundtrack|album=Descendants 3|rowheader=true|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| French Albums ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.snepmusique.com/tops-semaine/top-album-megafusion/?ye=2019&we=44|title=Le Top de la semaine : Top Albums Fusionnes \u2013 SNEP (Week 44, 2019)|publisher=[[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique]]|language=French|accessdate=November 5, 2019}}</ref>\n| 166\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Spanish Albums ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/4222-%C3%81lbumes-semana-45-2019|title=Top 100 Albumes \u2013 Semana 45: del 01.11.2019 al 07.11.2019|publisher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=November 13, 2019}}</ref>\n| 82\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]]<ref name=\"billboard200\">{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/business/chart-beat/8527130/drake-achieves-ninth-no-1-album-on-billboard-200-chart-with|title=Drake Achieves Ninth No. 1 Album on Billboard 200 Chart With 'Care Package'|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|date=August 11, 2019|accessdate=August 12, 2019}}</ref>\n| 7\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Kid Albums]] ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/kids-albums/2019-08-17|title=Soundtrack albums \u2013 August 17, 2017|work=Billboard|date=August 17, 2017 |accessdate=August 13, 2017}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US Soundtrack Albums ([[Billboard (magazine)|''Billboard'']])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/soundtracks/2019-08-17|title=Soundtrack albums \u2013 August 17, 2017|work=Billboard|date=August 17, 2017 |accessdate=August 13, 2017}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 200|''Rolling Stone'' Top 200]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/albums/2019-08-02/|title=Top 200 Albums|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|accessdate=March 1, 2020}}</ref>\n| 13\n|}\n\n== Home media ==\n''Descendants 3'' was released on [[DVD]] on August 6, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://amazonadviser.com/2019/07/18/disneys-descendants-3-dvd-august/|title=Disney\u2019s Descendants 3 comes home in August 2019|date=July 18, 2019|website=Amazon Adviser|access-date=2019-07-21}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{IMDb title|8022928}}\n\n{{Descendants franchise}}\n{{Disney Channel Original Movies}}\n{{Kenny Ortega}}\n\n[[Category:2010s fantasy films]]\n[[Category:2010s musical films]]\n[[Category:2019 television films]]\n[[Category:American fantasy films]]\n[[Category:American sequel films]]\n[[Category:Crossover films]]\n[[Category:Descendants (franchise)]]\n[[Category:Disney Channel Original Movie films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Kenny Ortega]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Vancouver]]\n[[Category:Television sequel films]]\n", "name_user": "Factfanatic1", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCast:The placement of China Anne McClain was off as after the main four she's the most major character yet the list was listed from most to least important. It's odd how she was last.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Descendants_3"}
