e=39|via=National Library Board |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Final standings==\nThe Asia Golf Circuit operated a points based system to determine the overall circuit champion, with points being awarded in each tournament to the leading players. At the end of the season, the player with the most points was declared the circuit champion, and there was a prize pool to be shared between the top players in the points table.\n{|class=wikitable\n|-\n!#!!Player!!Points <ref>{{cite news |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=LqclAAAAIBAJ&sjid=kQsEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6237%2C4368601|title=Minoza 4th in Asian Order of merit|newspaper=Manila Standard |location=Philippines |date=24 April 1989 |page=12|via=Google Archive |accessdate=9 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 1 || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Brian Claar]] ||  align=center|882\n|-\n| 2 || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Emlyn Aubrey]] || align=center|732\n|-\n| 3 || {{flagicon|MEX}} [[Carlos Espinosa]] ||  align=center|682\n|-\n| 4 || {{flagicon|PHI}} [[Frankie Minoza]] || align=center|638\n|-\n| 5 || {{flagicon|TWN}} [[Lu Chien-soon]] || align=center|595\n|-\n| 6 || {{flagicon|TWN}} [[Lu Hsi-chuen]] || align=center|595\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Asia Golf Circuit seasons}}\n\n[[Category:1989 in golf|Asia Golf Circuit]]\n[[Category:Asia Golf Circuit]]\n", "text_old": "{{use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\nThe '''1989 Asia Golf Circuit''' was the 28th season of [[golf]] tournaments that comprised the [[Asia Golf Circuit]].\n\nAmerican [[Brian Claar]] claimed the overall circuit championship.\n\n==Tournament schedule==\nThe table below shows the 1989 Asia Golf Circuit schedule.<ref>{{cite book |title=World of Professional Golf 1990 |first=Mark H. |last=McCormack |authorlink=Mark McCormack |publisher=Sackville |date=1990 |page=276\u2013284, 516\u2013527 |isbn=0948615389}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/44378544/1989-asia-golf-circuit/ |title=1989 Asia Golf Circuit |newspaper=Tampa Bay Times |location=St.Pe